bug.short_desc: failure to stop docker daemon on reboot
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1262771 Full journal from reboot
Description of problem:
I get the system into a state where docker won't stop and it has to be SIGKILL before reboot can happen.
``` Mar 14 03:15:27 cloudhost.localdomain systemd[1]: docker-containerd.service: State 'stop-final-sigterm' timed out. Killing. Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): ``` [root@cloudhost ~]# rpm -q docker docker-1.12.6-6.gitae7d637.fc25.x86_64 [root@cloudhost ~]# [root@cloudhost ~]# rpm-ostree status State: idle Deployments: ● fedora-atomic:fedora-atomic/25/x86_64/testing/docker-host Version: 25.86 (2017-03-14 01:11:30) Commit: af1ff84b2c6d3919e90f867fe2011fd3a5f78ac6e6309fd5dbb5e29ecd53c04c OSName: fedora-atomic
fedora-atomic:fedora-atomic/25/x86_64/docker-host Version: 25.67 (2017-02-27 22:34:22) Commit: ba95a4665776b58d342ad9cc367111179f9b8fcf19c6606f8964a8ec1622cadc OSName: fedora-atomic ```
Steps to Reproduce: 1. boot atomic host 2. run kubernetes on top - i use these ansible playbooks: https://github.com/kubernetes/contrib/tree/master/ansible 3. start an application 4. attempt to reboot
Note that this happens with either device mapper or overlay as the storage backend.

seems like it's not an issue - at least for devicemapper on f25 atomic host:
